  "body": "* py-evm Version: current master\r\n\r\n### What is wrong?\r\n\r\n`HeaderDB.persist_header_chain` iterates twice over the headers which fails if they are given in the form of an iterator.\r\n\r\nFirst loop: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/eth/db/header.py#L219-L227\r\nSecond loop: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/eth/db/header.py#L240-L251\r\nIt also extracts the first element: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/master/eth/db/header.py#L214\r\n\r\nThe same is bug is present in `eth.beacon.db.chain._persist_block_chain` where I originally encountered it.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nI can see three simple fixes:\r\n- Handle everything in a single loop\r\n- Convert the iterable to a tuple in the beginning\r\n- Change the type hint to only accept sequences",
